cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.CV 

The paper discusses reinforcement learning agents and their ability to remember observations and actions across sizable time intervals. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions backpropagation through time (BPTT), which is a common technique used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV), indicating that these sub-categories are also likely.
